PRESIDENT John Magufuli has appointed former President Benjamin Mkapa to be the chancellor of the University of Dodoma (UDOM). A statement released by the State House Communications Director Gerson Msigwa pointed out that the former third phase president, Mr Mkapa, will hold the post successively for two term. The president has also appointed Professor Ignas Aloys Rubaratuka to be the Tanzania Ports Authority (TPA) Board Chairman. Professor Rubaratuka once held the post, and will continue with it for two terms in a row. According to Mr Msigwaâ€™s statement the appointment started on May 10, 2019.